# Cloud ERP build context — only `backend/` + `frontend/` are needed.
# Without this file Railway copies the entire repo (~2 GB locally) into
# the Docker context, blowing up image size and stalling the registry
# push at ~933 MB. Incident 2026-05-07: 2-hour outage caused by this.

# --- Sibling systems that ship from their own repos / pipelines ---
factory-server/
weighbridge/
biometric-bridge/
opcserver/
rag-service/
mspil-brain/

# --- Local-only research / data (also gitignored) ---
vision/
db-backups/
.agents/
.codex/
.claude/

# --- Git + GitHub ---
.git/
.github/
.gitignore

# --- Docs not needed in container ---
docs/
*.md
*.pdf
AGENTS.md
CLAUDE.md
DESIGN.md
AUDIT_FUEL_PO_2026-04-01.md
DDGS_Logistics_Process.pdf
MSPIL_Procurement_Manual.pdf

# --- Node tooling caches / build outputs that get rebuilt anyway ---
**/node_modules/
**/.next/
**/.turbo/
**/.cache/
**/.parcel-cache/
**/dist/
**/build/
**/.vite/

# --- Editor / OS ---
**/.DS_Store
**/.vscode/
**/.idea/
**/*.swp
**/*.swo

# --- Logs + tmp ---
**/*.log
**/logs/
**/tmp/
**/temp/

# --- Local env files (Railway injects via Variables) ---
**/.env
**/.env.local
**/.env.*.local

# --- Test artifacts ---
**/coverage/
**/.nyc_output/
**/__tests__/
**/test-results/

# --- Python venvs (some sibling tools have these) ---
**/.venv/
**/venv/
**/__pycache__/
**/*.pyc

# --- CI / scripts that don't run in container ---
.deploy
docker-compose.yml
Dockerfile.local
*.dockerignore.local

# --- Backend uploads dir — runtime state, not built artifacts ---
backend/uploads/
backend/public/

# --- Misc ---
assets/
